for_label_override_hi": "", "description_zh_hans": "", "description_pa": "", "description_hi": "", "description_override_zh_hans": "", "description_override_pa": "", "description_override_hi": ""}, "description": "<p>Before Peter Jackson’s 2001 trilogy, other studios attempted to adapt <i>The Lord of the Rings </i>, to no avail. But the influence was still felt in Ron Howard’s <i>Willow</i> starring Warwick Davis as the titular character who was heavily inspired by Tolkein’s work.</p>"}], "published": true, "shape": null}